 use till 52+.  Too short to be of much use but might as well use this or Resistant on Naggy raids and such.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> LEVEL 52: THE DISCIPLINE OF EVASIVE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Bad - You'll only use this when you need to tank until you ding 55 and get tha vastly superior Defensive<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> LEVEL 53: THE DISCIPLINE OF CHARGE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Bad - For those raids where you're not gonna be doing any tanking (cuz there's lots of much higher warriors on the raid than you).  Might as well use this till 54<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> LEVEL 54: THE DISCIPLINE OF MIGHTY STRIKE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Good - Most effective when you are berserk.  I still use this quite a bit, even at 60.  You'll use this on high regen mobs where fast damage is of the essence, at least till 58<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> LEVEL 55: THE DISCIPLINE OF DEFENSIVE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Ub3r!!! - Our class defining disc.  Learn it, love it, because you will use this more than any other disc.  For 3 min you are a much better thank than you already are.  Always use this when I am main tank on an ubermob (with a few rare exceptions).<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> LEVEL 56: THE DISCIPLINE OF FURIOUS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Good - This is the one I use when I am not using Defensive.  It's useful against mobs who have a proc a lot worse than their melee damage (for example VS).  A mob can only proc if it lands a hit ... with this it won't be landing any so it won't proc.  Also remember to equip a nice damage 2H weapon if you can before activating this ... you'll do quite a bit of extra damage since you'll just hit once for every time the mob tries to hit you (regardless of your weapon's delay).  Also good for saving your butt when the cleric hasn't been paying attention and starts that CH late.  It lasts 9 sec so if you react quick it will keep you alive long enough for that CH to land.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> LEVEL 57: THE DISCIPLINE OF PRECISION</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Bad - This only comes in handy on high HP mobs (&gt;32k) and on which you are not tanking.  Thing is unless you are in a high-end guild filled with warriors higher than you, by this time you will be tanking on raids.  I've never parsed it, but I expect on a 3+ min fight it will add more damage than using Mightystrike<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> LEVEL 58: THE DISCIPLINE OF FELL STRIKE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Ok - An alternative to Mightystrike for high regen mobs.  Has the advantage of not needing to be berserk to get the most damage out of it.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> LEVEL 59: THE DISCIPLINE OF FORTITUDE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Bad - Unlike Furious this protects you from attacks from any direction (including back), but it doesn't do any damage to mobs (no ripostieing).  Never seen much use in this except perhaps if you're running to zone with a nasty train on you or something like that.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> LEVEL 60: THE DISCIPLINE OF AGGRESSIVE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Bad (would be Ok, but too late to be of any use) - Would be a nice discipline to use on high HP mobs on which you aren't tanking ...  But by level 60 you will very likely be tanking on any such mob. <p><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=18807" target="CRProfile" alt="Yunna's Profile" title="Yunna's Profile"><img src="http://24.101.174.177/scripts/rsig/yunnasig.php" border="0" alt=""></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucandiemandarkryder.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Candieman Darkryder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here..